

alt + enter  :  hint
alt + enter  : if pressed on if--->  invert if
To join two lines into one and remove unnecessary spaces, press Ctrl+Shift+J.
ctrl+w  select loops
ctrl alt m --->> extract to a method 
shift f6  ---> rename 
ctrl alt a 
ctrl alt c --.extract a constant
cltr alt v ---extract a variable
ctrl alt n ---> inline in a line instead of a variable ---> can be used to remove code from a function inline

cltr shift del  --> unwrap if

cltr shift i --> code completion tip

ctrl  F4  --> close the file
ctrl alt B  --> go into impl class
ctrl F3  , shift F3 ---> to track the selected text/word

To compare any two files or folders, select them in the Project tool window and press Ctrl+D.



ctrl alt L  : indentation
ctrl alt shift L :for indentation of selected code block


alt 9 to view git history
cltrl k to send to git


ctrl alt o  :remov unused imports
alt F1      show file in project tree

In the editor, press Ctrl+W/ Ctrl+Shift+W to extend or shrink your current code selection.

ctrl R find and replace

ctrl shift -/+   to collapse/uncollapse all methods 

file search: ctrl +shift+N 
Shift + shift:  global search

 Ctrl+Shift+E to get a list of recently viewed or changed code fragments.
 
 
